-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Arabtec Holding and Emaar Properties Moved
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-05-03T11:37:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/persian-gulf-stocks-arabtec-holding-and-emaar-properties-moved.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  fell 0.9 percent
to 1,582.09, the lowest level since Feb. 20, at the 2 p.m. close
in the emirate. The measure fell 4.2 percent this week. Abu
Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  declined 0.2 percent today.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Arabtec Holding Co. (ARTC)   fell for a second day,
dropping 0.9 percent to 3.44 dirhams. The United Arab Emirates’
biggest construction company said its board will meet May 8 to
elect a chairman and vice chairman.  Emaar Properties PJSC (EMAAR)   retreated to the lowest
level in a month, dropping 1.3 percent to 3.11 dirhams. The
company plans to start building two residential developments in
Dubai near the world’s tallest skyscraper, MEED magazine
reported May 2, citing industry sources it didn’t identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
